			<description><![CDATA[<p>MID-LEVEL INTERACTION DESIGNER<br />JOB DESCRIPTION<br />Sequence helps build products by providing integrated strategy and design services to emerging companies and brands in transition. With a focus on new technologies and consumer markets, we deliver innovative and effective work across a broad range of assignments &ndash; from strategy to identity, print and interactive design.</p><p>WE&rsquo;RE LOOKING FOR<br />passionate and pragmatic designers who are eager to join a fun, collaborative and innovative team. The Mid-Level Interaction Designer is a strategic problem solver who works with the larger team to bridge the gap between user needs, business objectives, and technical requirements to create compelling and understandable experiences. This position will work closely with clients during projects defining problems by asking the right questions and effectively communicating the solutions.&nbsp;</p><p>QUALIFICATIONS<br />&bull; This position requires a minimum of 1-4 years experience in a service-oriented organization.&nbsp; (Academic time and projects could be deemed applicable if the hiring manager feels it is appropriate.)<br />&bull; Ownership of the interaction design aspect of a project with a check-ins by senior staff.<br />&bull; Experience creating simple, impactful design deliverables that effectively communicates design thinking.&nbsp; (We use Omnigraffle for almost all IxD deliverables so there should be an expectation to use this tool.)<br />&bull; Firm knowledge of user experience best practices.<br />&bull; Familiarity and ongoing interest to learn interaction patterns for a variety of platforms (HTML5 for the web, iOS, Android, etc.)<br />&bull; Ability to think of an experience end-to-end while considering the variety of states and dependencies that data and logic driven products require.&nbsp;<br />&bull; A comfort level working closely with both visual designers and software developers.<br />&bull; A portfolio that demonstrates strategic thinking and compelling solutions for a variety of problems.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Strong attention to detail and exceptional organization, logic, and analytical skills.<br />&bull; Ability to multi-task and prioritize tasks; comfortable with tight deadlines.</p><p><br />&emsp;<br />RESPONSIBILITIES<br />Work the with the client and team to determine project requirements and success factors, which can include:<br />&bull; Persona creation, coupled with defining user stories, task flow creation, user needs analysis, and scenario development<br />&bull; Assist in the process of defining the clients business needs<br />&bull; Help guide the definition of the project&rsquo;s technical specifications including, but not limited, to establishing the features and functionality contained within the experience.&nbsp;<br />&bull; Drive the definition of any technical limitations and capabilities that will affect the user experience (types of content available from the client, transactional flows required by system integration, etc.)</p><p>During the design period, the interaction designer will:<br />&bull; Translate the user &amp; business requirements into intuitive interface solutions.<br />&bull; Maintain a thorough understanding of backend systems and capabilities.<br />&bull; Develop application maps, process flows, wire frames and mockups with accompanying annotations.<br />&bull; Help define interaction rules based on a synthesis of user needs, technical restrictions and requirements and business goals/needs.<br />&bull; Support user research/usability testing and allow for iterative design</p><p><br />ADDITIONAL COMPETENCIES DESIRED<br />&bull; Although the position is titled Interaction your skill-set will ideally include some level of information architecture (information organization, taxonomies)<br />&bull; Graphic design background<br />&bull; Familiarity with presentation layer code and application layer design<br />&bull; Experience with quick prototyping for testing and client review using a variety of tools (Axure, Fireworks, Flash, etc.)<br />&bull; Experience conducting user research</p>]]></description>
